HEADWORD: Distringas
<hw>Dis*trin"gas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., that you
distrain, fr. <ets>distringere</ets>. See <er>Distrain</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A writ commanding the sheriff to distrain a person
by his goods or chattels, to compel a compliance with something required
of him.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Distrouble</ent>⟦br⟧
